      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REGAL SAINT (2) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by a nose at Q Straight in a handy 19.16. Has a low draw and likes the trip. Looks the testing material. KICKER WILDCARD (1) is worth forgiving for his last effort when fourth (16.93) at Q Straight over 300m. Cannot be underestimated. GEMSTONE JASPER (8) doesn't show much early dash but winds into his races and is overdue, hitting the line hard to place latest (20.01) in a Grade 5 at this track and making it three minors in a row. Winning chance. MAJESTIC ONE (3) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when third (21.97) at this track in a Grade 5.",
